The paper focuses on analyzing political discussions on Twitter during the Indian General Elections in 2014 and 2019, which involves social media analysis (cs.SOC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The authors also compare the usage of Twitter by different political parties and politicians, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) categories. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing data and patterns, which could be categorized under social computing (cs.SI).
